Walk Walk Dance
properties.desc: Created for and during the pandemic, Walk Walk Dance is a series of music-making lines that explore how participation and interaction can create new spaces for play even amidst physical distancing rules and COVid-19 protocols.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Nil Nil
properties.desc: Nil:Nil is a portrait of play in pandemic times. As our work and play move online, our human interactions become subject to a comprehensive enframing.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Jax
properties.desc: Jax by Pierre Poussin reimagines one of the  oldest and most widespread games in the world by amplifying its scale and colour, inviting visitors to see the game anew.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Double Driblle
properties.desc: Through the illogical use of basketball motifs, Toronto artist Esmaa Mohamoud transforms The Bentway into a surreal basketball court.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Big Red
properties.desc: Inspired by a now-famous drawing by Bo Bardi, this project interprets and makes real one of the play sculptures from her original illustration, acting as a device to challenge the civic context found at The Bentway.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Weweni Bizindan
properties.desc: Continuing their practice of re-installing Anishinaabe place-names throughout the roads, highways, trails and paths of Toronto, the Ogimaa Mikana Project (Susan Blight and Hayden King) offers a new dialogue with the street.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: WEEPING CONCRETE
properties.desc: WEEPING CONCRETE is a site-specific project for a trio of performers across two towering scaffolds; asking us to reflect on the streets as we know them and imagine what they might be.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Parade
properties.desc: Part of the delight of being on the street is in not knowing what you will encounter next…  Inspired by the dynamic convergences and events that transpire in our streets, PARADE is a kinetic installation that infuses the Bentway’s skate trail with the vitality of the city and the ever shifting variables of the streetscape
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: And With
properties.desc: And Walk is a sound walk that invites audiences and passersby to experience the sounds and textures of The Bentway, the streets nearby, and the rumbling urban artery above like never before
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Confluence
properties.desc: Inspired by the water systems that have shaped Toronto, Confluence invites visitors to flow through an engrossing convergence of natural and human-made forces.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Receipts
properties.desc: Receipts is a multimodal interface that receives (via voice, video, and/or text), anonymizes, archives, and performs (on the web and in public) the testimony of people that have experienced or witnessed anti-Asian aggression in public spaces.

properties.title: Radical Love
properties.desc: A multimedia installation that centres Black and Afro-Indigenous Trans women and non-binary people, creating monuments to Trans lives and their survival.

properties.title: Sinaaqpagiaqtutt
properties.desc: Sinaaqpagiaqtuut/The Long-Cut is a procession that began in Kinngait (Cape Dorset, Nunavut) and continues in Toronto

properties.title: Museum of the Moon
properties.desc: The Bentway brings the Moon under the Gardiner with a presentation of Museum of the Moon: a seven-metre wide touring sculptural work by UK artist Luke Jerram, which fuses lunar imagery to bring the surface of the moon to life on earth.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Distribution of Sensation
properties.desc: Mimicking the drainage infrastructure of The Bentway (the PVC pipes that carry rainwater down from the Gardiner Expressway) Mitchell Akiyama and Brady Peters have created a series of sonic sculptures that pose as infrastructure, albeit of an unusual sort.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Hoarding
properties.desc: In “Hoarding,” hazard tape—a material typically used to keep people away from spaces under construction—will wrap a series of “bents” that hold up the Gardiner Expressway.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Halcyon
properties.desc: Halcyon is a video and dance performance designed to question the range of ways in which we constantly tune and adjust our self-presentation, both onscreen and in real life.
properties.See More: Click here for more info

properties.title: Theory X
properties.desc: Together, Monument Lab and The Bentway have posed an open research question: What is your theory of Toronto? We have worked with Lum and Farber to create a list of potential speakers to reflect a widespread critical community.

properties.title: Block Party
properties.desc: A family-friendly day-long celebration

properties.title: New Monuments for New Cities
properties.desc: This day-long public event introduced the public to the New Monuments exhibition, the contributing artists from several participating cities, and the issues the exhibition raises.

properties.title: Izhininjiiniwag
properties.desc: Izhininjiiniwag is an amalgamation of skateboard culture, pow wow regalia and photography

properties.title: Derives
properties.desc: Celebrating the repurposed architecture of the Gardiner Expressway via The Bentway, this site-specific performance re-envisions the site as a group navigation, questioning urban infrastructure as forms of political power and social design.

properties.title: Shift

properties.title: Every Building from a Defunct Liberty Village Factory, Rotated Vertically

properties.desc: Marking the inaugural collaboration with neighbouring Exhibition Place and the Bentway, Pulse Topology by Rafael Lozano-Hemmers will take over a massive, enclosed storage chamber nestled beneath the Gardiner Expressway, inviting the public to discover a striking, industrial part of the city for the first time.
